{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Scrap PIP & ESA assessments for anyone receiving palliative care",
        "additional_details": "People with incurable cancers are being sent for assessments to get back to work. Paramedic assessors state people are curable when oncologists know the truth. There's already a lack of support for those dying. No nurses for secondaries until 2020 so we\u2019re told !!! Why make this more stressful?",
        "background": "No-one receiving palliative care, whether or not they qualify for DS1500, should have to jump through the hoops DWP assessors set which can stop them receiving benefits.",
